  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison is replying to a letter he received from Mrs. Friend in which she expressed concern for Henry Clarke Wright&apos;s health. Mrs. Friend is a medium and claims to have had a clairvoyant vision of Henry Clarke Wright on shipboard and in great distress. Mrs. Friend heard that Garrison is a believer in psychic phenomena. Garrison believes that at Henry Clarke Wright&apos;s age, he will suffer greatly from seasickness. Since Garrison spoke to Wright, he has abandoned the idea of going to England.</subfield>
